      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know you said to go to the clinic but its like 10pm and the nearest place is so far away. plus it doesnt look *that* deep once i press on it, it just keeps seeping. i've read online that manuka honey is actually used in hospitals for wound healing because it's so effective. if i just use a really thick layer, won't that basically act like a seal and stop the bleeding and keep the bacteria out? it seems way safer than sitting in an emergency room all night for something that might just be a scratch.",
